# 1. 週末の予定は

Honami: That was delicious.
Saki: That was so good! Ahh, I'm stuffed!
Ichika: Oh, what should we do about practice this weekend?
Shiho: Yeah, we haven't set a meeting time yet, have we?
Saki: We have the studio from two... So, why don't we meet up a bit early and have lunch together?
Honami: Oh...
Saki: Hona?
Honami: Ah, I'm sorry. I might actually arrive late.
Honami: My neighborhood association is getting together that day.
Ichika: Your neighborhood association...? They put on seasonal events and stuff, right? Locally organized cherry blossom viewing parties immediately come to mind...
Saki: Oh, they also put on hiking events and fun festivals! No fair! I wanna join!
Honami: Haha... I won't be participating in an event this time around. I'll be representing my parents at an association meeting.
Saki: What?! You're gonna be in a meeting?
Shiho: Now that you mention it, this isn't the first time you've done this for them, is it...?
Honami: I only do this on occasion. Usually during the periods when our shop is at its busiest.
Saki: But you get to speak for your mom and dad! You're such a grown-up, Hona!
Ichika: So, what are you going to discuss at this meeting?
Honami: This time, we'll be discussing a picture-book reading.
Saki: A picture-book reading...?!
Saki: Hehe. I remember how you read me all those stories when we were little and I was still in the hospital, Hona...
Saki: You always put such a big smile on my face.
Honami: Hehe. I also had fun watching your eyes twinkle each time.
Shiho: Does this mean you're gonna be the one telling stories, Honami?
Honami: No, our veteran storyteller will be handling that. I'll probably be helping out behind the scenes.
Ichika: You seem really excited about this, Honami...
Honami: Huh? D-Do I?
Saki: Yeah, the way you're smiling says it all!
Honami: I actually attended one of these readings before when I was little...
Honami: That was where I learned about this story I really love, and they're going to be telling it during this event.
Ichika: Really?
Saki: So that's why you're so excited♪
Honami: Yes!
Honami: (I'm looking forward to this event so much.)
Honami: (I'll need to do everything I can in order to make it a great one.)
Association Chair: Thank you all for taking time out of your busy schedules to gather here today.
Association Chair: About the reading event we'll be holding next month... We've run into a slight problem, and I'd like to discuss it with all of you today.
Honami: Huh...?
Honami: (A problem? What happened...?)
Association Chair: Unfortunately, Endo, our designated storyteller, likely won't be able to join us for this event...
Association Chair: So, we'll need to make an emergency swap.
Association Chair: I'd like to begin by asking for volunteers. Would any of you care to be our storyteller?
Honami: ...
Honami: (To be the storyteller...)
Honami: (I did tell a few stories when I went to shadow over at that kindergarten, but this event is on a completely different scale...)
Honami: (Still...)
Honami: I actually attended one of these readings before when I was little...
Honami: That was where I learned about this story I really love, and they're going to be telling it during this event.
Honami: E-Excuse me...!
Honami: If it's alright, I'd like to volunteer!
